::Zardus::

Zardus enters the lab, stepping on some glass as he does so. He frowns, 
looking around. Everything was shattered! Zardus' eyes widen, looking at the 
femm, still strapped on the table.

The Alliance commander frowns again, looking around the lab. There was no 
other explanation, the femm must have somehow broken every piece of glass in 
the room, including the lights.

Zardus walks over to a console, frowning at the shattered screen. He taps a 
few keys on his wrist comp, the bonds on the female releasing.

Zardus walks over to her. The scanners reported that she was awake, and that 
the new programming has kicked in.

"Welcome to the Alliance," he says, coming up to the table, "I must 
congratulate you on the job you did with the glass in this room."
